{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981973043,"sessionID":"ses_1cc697c48ffeRmAX4IVRPP82Ku","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_IinqJ0C8ePGthhxmXTlfa9eR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":400},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"This term has no enzyme xref: \\n\\nid: GO:0043713\\nname: (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity\\nnamespace: molecular_function\\ndef: \\\"Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoisocaproate + NADH + H+ = (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate + NAD+.\\\" [GOC:jl, PMID:16957230]\\nis_a: GO:0016616 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-OH group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor\\n\\n\\nBut \\\"(R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase\\\" is a synonym of EC:1.1.1.345 D-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD(+)), which equates with this GO term:\\n\\nid: GO:0140175\\nname: (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity\\nnamespace: molecular_function\\ndef: \\\"Catalysis of the reaction: a (2R)-2-hydroxycarboxylate + NAD+ = a 2-oxocarboxylate + NADH + H+.\\\" [RHEA:35643]\\nxref: EC:1.1.1.345 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:10052 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:35643 {source=\\\"skos:exactMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:57408 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:70327 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:86067 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nxref: RHEA:86071 {source=\\\"skos:narrowMatch\\\"}\\nis_a: GO:0016616 ! oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-OH group of donors, NAD or NADP as acceptor\\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \\\"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/30138\\\" xsd:anyURI\\n\\nAlso, a search of CHEBI with '(R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate' returns:\\nCHEBI:55534 - (R)-2-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoic acid\\n\\nAnd one of the narrowMatch RHEA xrefs is:\\nRHEA:10052\\n(2R)-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoate + NAD(+) = 4-methyl-2-oxopentanoate + NADH + H(+)\\n\\nand (2R)-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoate (CHEBI:55535) is the conjugate base of (R)-2-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoic acid (CHEBI:55534).\\n\\n\\nSo....I think GO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity should be obsoleted and replaced by GO:0140175 (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity\\n\\nGO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity has 0 annotations anyway.\",\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAn3fSg\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"raymond91125\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n10:       \"body\": \"Dear all, \\n\\nThe proposal has been made to obsolete GO:0043713 (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate dehydrogenase activity.\\n\\n* The reason for obsoletion is that this term is equivalent to GO:0140175 (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity.\\n\\nThere are no experimental annotations to this term.\\nThere are X InterPro2GO/UniRule/UniProtKW mappings to this term. \\nThis term is not present in any subset.\\n\\nThis term is being replaced by GO:0140175 (2R)-2-hydroxyacid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity\\n\\nIf obsolete term has a 'consider' term:  (optional)\\nAnnotations can be transferred to [suggested GO term(s)] \\n\\nAny comments can be  added to the issue: [link to GitHub ticket in the go-ontology tracker]. \\nUnless objections are received by [DATE], we will assume that you agree to this change.\\n\\nThanks, \\n\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-04-28T15:34:45Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31966#issuecomment-4336770890\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n18:     },\n19:     {\n20:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAkAHws8AAAABAn4Mfg\",\n21:       \"author\": {\n22:         \"logi